<div class="tip_number">TIP 208</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            An infant with swollen, tender fingers or toes may be showing the first signs of sickle cell disease. The early diagnosis of this disease and the treatment and/or prevention of accompanying infections (including additional immunizations) will reduce the child's risk of dying very young.
        </div>

</div>
